headline: CSX profit falls 22% but investors focus on the direction the new CEO will take the railroad
summary: Investors looked past a 22% drop in CSX’s third quarter earnings Thursday and focused on the direction the railroad’s new CEO might take it and the possibility of any strategic deals.  CEO Steve Angel promised to focus on making CSX the best-performing railroad.  Without promising a merger, Angel said he would consider any strategic opportunities that make sense for shareholders.

headline: CSX’s (NASDAQ:CSX) Q3 Earnings Results: Revenue In Line With Expectations
summary: Freight rail services provider CSX (NASDAQ:CSX) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, but sales were flat year on year at $3.59 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.44 per share was 3.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
